modules.description: This module implements a free monoid structure, supporting operations like concatenation (`plus`), flattening lists of monoids, and converting items or lists into monoidal values. It works with polymorphic data types, allowing construction and manipulation of sequences where associativity and an identity element are required. Concrete use cases include building extensible logging systems, accumulating values with associative operations, and representing sequences in a compositional manner.

This module constructs and manipulates Clang AST nodes for expressions, statements, and declarations. It provides operations to create binary operations, integer literals, and flattened lists of statements, as well as transforming declarations. It is used to generate and modify low-level C-like code structures within the AST for analysis or code generation tasks.
